        "text": "I understand if everyone wants to kick my ass for this but this is honestly one of my favourite films of all time. It's one of very few that I can watch over and over again and never grow tired of, even though I'm fully aware that it's severely unrealistic (NASA branded it \"absurd\") and probably politically questionable too (mainly because, despite continued assertions from certain characters that the act of selling tickets for placement on the arks is inhumane, most of the people who end up on the ships are billionaires anyway). Truthfully, my biggest criticism is that this film, at 158 minutes, isn't long enough. I'm also more than slightly peeved that the spin-off series never happened ðŸ˜¢â€¦"
